.Im MicroEmacs command|bind;command|help
.ds C0 "(\fB\*(cHa\fR)\ \&
.so me.tni
.TH command-apropos 2
.XI command-apropos - "\*(C0List commands involving a concept"
.SH NAME
command-apropos \- List commands involving a concept
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
.B command-apropos
"\fIstring\fR" (\fB\*(cHa\fR)
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B command-apropos
compiles a list of all commands with  \fIstring\fR  in their name, also giving
their current key bindings.  Only commands that are not hidden are  displayed,
if a numeric  argument  of 0 is  supplied  then all  commands  are  displayed,
irrespective of their visibility.
.SH EXAMPLE
To find all of the  commands  with  "\fCcommand\fR"  in their  name space then
issue the command  "\fC\*(cHa command\fR"  which  generates a list of commands
such as:-
.CS
abort-command ................. "C-g"
                                "esc C-g"
                                "C-x C-g"
command-apropos ............... "C-h a"
command-complete
execute-named-command ......... "esc x"
help-command .................. "C-h C-c"
ipipe-shell-command ........... "esc \\\\"
list-commands ................. "C-h c"
pipe-shell-command ............ "esc !"
                                "esc @"
                                "C-x @"
shell-command
.CE 0
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht describe-bindings 2 .
.ad
.rm C0
.FH
